TO BE ENTITLED
HB228 INTRODUCED
29 AN ACT
30
31 Relating to criminal procedure; to amend Sections
32 15-11-1 and 15-13-3, Code of Alabama 1975; to further provide
33 for preliminary hearings and further provide for pretrial
34 detention hearings; and to repeal Section 15-13-3.1, Code of
35 Alabama 1975, relating to pretrial detention.
36 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
37 Section 1. Sections 15-11-1 and 15-13-3, Code of
38 Alabama 1975, are amended to read as follows:
39 "§15-11-1
40 (a) Every person individual charged with and arrested
41 for a felony before his or her indictment shall have an
42 absolute right to a preliminary hearing on said the charge
43 upon such person's his or her demand within 30 45 days
44 following said the arrest;, provided, that such person's his
45 or her failure or refusal to appear for such the preliminary
46 hearing or his or her absence from the state at the time of
47 the setting for the preliminary hearing shall not delay or
48 invalidate an indictment pursuant to said the charge.
49 (b) A pretrial detention hearing held pursuant to
50 Section 15-13-3 shall satisfy a defendant's rights under this
51 section unless otherwise ordered by the court for good cause
52 shown."
53 "§15-13-3
54 (a) A defendant is not eligible for bail when he or she
55 is charged with capital murder pursuant to Section 13A-5-40,
56 if the court is of the opinion, on the evidence adduced, that
