58 (b)(1) The court, after After a pretrial detention
59 hearing as provided in this subsection, for an offense
60 enumerated in this subsection and after the presentment of an
61 indictment or a showing of probable cause in the charged
62 offense, and if the court may deny a defendant bail if both of
63 the following apply:
64 (1) The prosecuting attorney proves by clear and
65 convincing evidence that no condition or combination of
66 conditions of release will reasonably ensure the defendant's
67 appearance in court or protect the safety of the community or
68 any person, may deny a defendant's bail, if he or she.
