93 (2)(c)(1) A court shall order that a defendant charged
94 with an offense listed in this subsection (b) be held without
95 bail prior to a pretrial detention hearing, unless the court
96 is notified that there is an agreement between the parties
97 regarding conditions of bail.
98 (2) If there is an agreement regarding bail, no
99 pretrial detention hearing shall be held.
100 (3)(d)(1) The court shall hold a pretrial detention
101 hearing immediately, upon the defendant's first appearance
102 before the court, shall set a pretrial detention hearing
103 within 10 days of the arrest of a defendant for an offense
104 listed in subsection (b)unless the prosecuting attorney or the
105 defendant requests a continuance. Except for good cause, a
106 continuance on a motion of the defendant may not exceed five
107 days, excluding Saturdays, Sundays, and state holidays, and a
108 continuance on motion by the prosecuting attorney may not
109 exceed three days, excluding Saturdays, Sundays, and state
110 holidays.
111 (2) A pretrial detention hearing may be continued for
112 up to 21 days upon a determination of good cause.
