169 whether there is an adequate record for purposes of appellate
170 review.
171 (7)a.(i)(1) A prosecuting attorney may file a motion
172 for a pretrial detention hearing at any time.
173 b.(2) A pretrial detention hearing may be reopened,
174 before or after a determination by the court, at any time
175 prior to trial if the court finds that information exists that
176 was not known by the movant at the time of the pretrial
177 detention hearing.
178 (8)(j) In an order denying bail, the judge shall make
179 written findings or state for the record findings of fact and
180 a statement of the reasons for denying bail. The judge shall
181 enter an order denying bail within 48 hours of the pretrial
182 detention hearing.
183 (k) An appeal of a pretrial detention order shall be
184 made to the Court of Criminal Appeals unless there is not an
185 adequate record, in which case the appeal shall be made to the
186 circuit court de novo.
187 (l)(1) Notwithstanding any provision of law, a judge
188 may order, as a condition of bond, that a defendant charged
189 with any offense listed in subsection (b) be supervised by the
190 Board of Pardons and Paroles.
191 (2) The board shall adopt rules necessary to implement
192 this subsection."
